    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1891-12-03T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1891-12-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="242" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d242">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Blaine</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Egan</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1891-12-03">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 3,
                            1891</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Blaine instructs Mr. Egan to report who asked him for his testimony in
                        the <hi rend="italic">Baltimore</hi> case, which, according to telegraphic
                        advice received by the Chilean minister from the foreign office, was
                        requested of him twenty days ago and not given.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
